{"time":"2026-04-25T05:07:04.310Z","event":"run_finished","provider":"tavily","taskId":"agent-search-benchmark-methodology","metrics":{"provider":"tavily","taskId":"agent-search-benchmark-methodology","toolCalls":8,"searchCalls":7,"fetchCalls":1,"failedCalls":0,"totalConnectMs":1259,"totalCallLatencyMs":31942,"argumentTokens":639,"rawOutputTokens":54848,"normalizedEvidenceTokens":14486,"totalTrajectoryTokens":58239,"contract":{"toolCount":5,"searchToolCount":2,"fetchToolCount":1,"descriptionTokens":143,"schemaTokens":2277,"totalMcpFootprintTokens":2752,"hasFreshnessControl":true,"hasSourcePolicyControl":true,"hasContentBudgetControl":true,"hasUsageMetadata":false}},"semanticScore":{"agentModel":"gpt-5.5 xhigh","provider":"tavily","taskId":"agent-search-benchmark-methodology","success":true,"answerSupportedByEvidence":true,"retrievalQualityScore":4.4,"agentExperienceScore":4.2,"sourcePolicyAdherent":null,"freshnessAdherent":null,"callRationale":"Started by inspecting Tavily's MCP schema and selected tavily_search for source discovery plus tavily_extract for primary-page follow-up. Used focused domain-filtered searches for Exa, Parallel, and Tavily/GitHub, then narrowed Tavily's benchmark repository and docs because the first Tavily-specific query returned unrelated GitHub noise. Extracted primary pages once the key URLs were identified and added one bounded Exa evaluation-guide lookup for explicit benchmark/latency guidance.","strengths":["Recovered all expected benchmark terms: SimpleQA, WISER, MS Marco/MSMARCO, and document relevance.","Hit the expected source domains: exa.ai, parallel.ai, github.com, and docs.tavily.com.","Collected primary/public evidence from Exa benchmark pages, Parallel WISER/Search MCP benchmark pages, Tavily's public search-evals repository, and Tavily search-depth docs.","Tavily's domain filters, search_depth control, raw-content option, and extract tool made source targeting and follow-up possible through the MCP provider alone."],"weaknesses":["The first Tavily benchmark search returned unrelated GitHub repositories and required an exact follow-up for tavily-ai/tavily-search-evals.","The broad GitHub raw-content follow-up produced a very large raw response, which hurt context efficiency even though the normalized evidence was useful.","The extract normalization for the multi-URL extraction was sparse, so some useful supporting details came from raw search snippets rather than compact normalized evidence."],"notableFailures":["Direct fix and needs no further changes: the first harness call used an args path before the JSON files were present in the requested workdir, so it failed locally before contacting Tavily. I moved the args files to the correct evals/work run directory and continued.","Direct fix and needs no further changes: the initial Tavily-specific search missed the expected tavily-ai repository; an exact follow-up query found the repository and run_evaluation.py.","Fixed but could benefit from cleaner/simpler implementation with an architectural change: using include_raw_content=true on a GitHub search produced a 36k-token raw response. A better harness pattern would cap raw content or prefer extract with a query on known primary URLs."],"confidence":0.88},"artifact":"report.json"}
